Of Cyprus left, to Paphos’ Isle they tend, With their bright load, and ever as they move, Owning her genial sway, they gently bend, And twine their neeks in spiral folds of love3 Thus ’neath Valhalla‘s domes the bright Valkyres rove.

But eease, my Muse, to touch so soft a string;

Let thy great theme more lofty thoughts inspiro,

Some stirring influence o'er thy numbers fling,

And wake to ecstasy thy slumbering fire.

Nor fear that she whom erst thou didst desire

To ayd thy drooping pinion, did not hear,

Nor Odin will refuse to swell thy lyre

With notes of combat loud, and fierce, and dream Lo! he is at thy side, and bids thee banish fear.
